<topic id='element_opcs-4_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: OPCS-4 CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
    <dl>
      <dlentry>
        <dt>Format / Length</dt>
        <dd>an4</dd>
      </dlentry>
    </dl>

  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_opcs-4_code">OPCS-4 CODE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_clinical_classification_code">CLINICAL CLASSIFICATION CODE</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>
      <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_opcs-4_code">OPCS-4 CODE</xref>
 is the 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS_Classification_of_Interventions_and_Procedures</xref>
 (
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
) code which is used to identify the 
    <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_coded_clinical_entry">CODED CLINICAL ENTRY</xref>
.  </p>
  <p>Notes:</p>
  <ul>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
Where a 
                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_patient_procedure">Patient Procedure</xref>
 is carried out and required for reporting using the 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
 classification, every effort must be made to report the appropriate 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
 code in the Out-Patient Attendance Commissioning Data Set.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
      <li>
         <div>
            <p>
Where providers locally use 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/supporting_information/clinical_coding/opcs_classification_of_interventions_and_procedures.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">OPCS-4</xref>
 codes with a fifth character added, this should be removed before inclusion in the 
                <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/web_site_content/cds_supporting_information/commissioning_data_sets_introduction.asp"
                     scope="external"
                     format="html">Commissioning Data Set</xref>
.        </p>
         </div>
      </li>
  </ul>


